WorkItem.ClosedComment: The talent string is different because the Glyph of Quick Decay was added in Rawr 2.3.5 - so basically, this must be fixed in Simcraft. (or to put it another way, its not actually a rawr bug).
WorkItem.Description:
Greeting all,
Since version 2.3.5 of Rawr, the Warlock model file is wrong when exporting to SimCraft.
 
Glyphe on my char in Rawr:
Conflagrate, Life tap, Incinerate
 
Glyphes when imported to SimCraft:
Conflagrate, Life tap, Metaporphosis
 
Here is the diff between the talents line in Rawr files:
Wrong one (Rawr 2.3.11):
<WarlockTalents>000000000000000000000000000003310030003000000000000000005203205210331051335230351.01000000011000000</WarlockTalents>
Right one (Rawr 2.3.4):
<WarlockTalents>000000000000000000000000000003310030003000000000000000005203205210331051335230351.0100000011000000</WarlockTalents>
 
Thank a lot for your hard work.
